The paper focuses on improving relation extraction using pre-trained language representations, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The use of deep learning models and unsupervised pre-training also suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves modeling long-range dependencies between entity mentions, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on two datasets, which suggests that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) could also be a relevant sub-category.
